---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header     from '../components/astro/Header.astro';
import Footer     from '../components/astro/Footer.astro';
import Accordion  from '../components/astro/Accordion.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Prostate Hub - Stage 4">
  <Header />
  
  <main class="my-8">
    <section class="text-center p-8 mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Stage 4: Metastatic Prostate Cancer</h1>
      <p class="text-lg max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        Comprehensive information about Stage 4 prostate cancer, treatment approaches, and support resources for patients and families.
      </p>
    </section>
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8">
      <div class="md:w-1/3 border border-gray-200 bg-fuchsia rounded-lg p-4">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Statistics</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p>Approximately 8% of men are diagnosed with Stage 4 prostate cancer, called "de novo" metastatic disease.</p>
          <p>The 5-year survival rate for metastatic prostate cancer is around 30%, though newer treatments are improving these outcomes.</p>
          <p>In New Zealand, approximately 350 men are diagnosed with de novo Stage 4 prostate cancer annually.</p>
          <div class="h-32 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
            [Chart Placeholder: Treatment Response in Stage 4]
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    <div class="md:w-2/3">

      <Accordion title="What is Stage 4 Prostate Cancer?" initiallyOpen={true}>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p>Stage 4 prostate cancer means the cancer has spread beyond the prostate to distant parts of the body. At this stage:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>The cancer has metastasized to other organs, lymph nodes, or bones</li>
            <li>PSA levels are typically very elevated</li>
            <li>The Gleason score is usually 8-10</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Stage 4 is further divided into:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li><strong>Stage 4A:</strong> Cancer has spread to nearby lymph nodes but not to distant organs</li>
            <li><strong>Stage 4B:</strong> Cancer has spread to distant lymph nodes, bones, or other organs</li>
          </ul>
          <p>While Stage 4 prostate cancer is not typically curable, many men live for years with good quality of life with proper treatment.</p>
        </div>
      </Accordion>
      
      <Accordion title="Treatment Approaches">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg">Androgen Deprivation Therapy (ADT)</h3>
          <p>The foundation of treatment for metastatic prostate cancer, including:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>LHRH agonists/antagonists (e.g., Goserelin, Degarelix)</li>
            <li>Anti-androgens (e.g., Bicalutamide)</li>
            <li>Complete androgen blockade (combination therapy)</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mt-6">Advanced Hormone Therapies</h3>
          <p>Second-generation hormone therapies that may be effective even when cancer becomes resistant to initial ADT:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Abiraterone acetate</li>
            <li>Enzalutamide</li>
            <li>Apalutamide</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mt-6">Chemotherapy</h3>
          <p>Often given alongside hormone therapy:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Docetaxel - usually the first chemotherapy option</li>
            <li>Cabazitaxel - may be used when docetaxel is no longer effective</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mt-6">Radiation Therapy</h3>
          <p>May be used to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Treat the primary tumor in newly diagnosed metastatic disease</li>
            <li>Relieve pain from bone metastases</li>
            <li>Target specific problematic metastases</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mt-6">Bone-Targeted Therapies</h3>
          <p>To strengthen bones and prevent complications:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Bisphosphonates (e.g., Zoledronic acid)</li>
            <li>Denosumab</li>
            <li>Radium-223 for bone metastases</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </Accordion>
      
      <Accordion title="Managing Side Effects">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p>Treatment for Stage 4 prostate cancer can cause significant side effects:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Hot flashes and night sweats</li>
            <li>Loss of bone density and increased fracture risk</li>
            <li>Fatigue</li>
            <li>Sexual dysfunction</li>
            <li>Changes in body composition</li>
            <li>Cognitive changes</li>
            <li>Cardiovascular effects</li>
            <li>Chemotherapy-specific side effects (nausea, hair loss, neuropathy)</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Discuss a comprehensive side effect management plan with your healthcare team.</p>
        </div>
      </Accordion>
      
      <Accordion title="New Zealand Support Resources">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p>Support is crucial for Stage 4 patients and their families:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li><a href="#" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Stage 4 Support Groups in New Zealand</a></li>
            <li><a href="#" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Psychological Support Services</a></li>
            <li><a href="#" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Palliative Care Services</a></li>
            <li><a href="#" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Financial Support and Benefits Information</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </Accordion>
      
      <Accordion title="Clinical Trials and Research">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p>New treatments are constantly being developed for metastatic prostate cancer:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li><a href="#" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Current Clinical Trials in New Zealand</a></li>
            <li><a href="#" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">International Trial Access Programs</a></li>
            <li><a href="#" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Emerging Therapies and Research Updates</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </Accordion>
      
      <Accordion title="Planning for the Future">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p>Important considerations for Stage 4 patients:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Advance care planning</li>
            <li>Legal and financial planning</li>
            <li>Communication with family about wishes and preferences</li>
            <li>Quality of life considerations in treatment decisions</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </Accordion>
    </div>
    
  </main>
  <div class="flex justify-center">
    <a href="/" class="px-6 py-3 bg-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-200 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg transition-colors">
      Return to Home
    </a>
  </div>
  
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>